      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Roofs having trusses rather than rafters, and beams or purlins, meaning the frame comprises a triangle-based webbing having the function to support the roof and tie the outside walls. Truss roofs may be wood or steel.</Note_Text>
